@title MultiRaffle
 @notice Single-winner raffle logic with a dynamic array of sold ticketNumbers.

@dev `RaffleSettings` for a single-winner raffle:
   - ticketSize: cost per ticket (wei)
   - numberRange: valid ticketNumbers in [1..numberRange]
   - houseTake: 0..100 (percentage)
   - raffleDuration: how long until raffleDeadline, in seconds

@dev Stores all data about a single raffle.
      `winnerPicked` becomes true once Chainlink picks the winner.
@dev For each minted NFT ticket, store which raffle & ticketNumber.

@notice For each raffle, store a dynamic array of sold ticketNumbers.
         e.g. soldTickets[raffleId] = [7, 42, 99, ...]
@notice tokenId => RaffleTicket info (which raffle, which ticketNumber).
@dev global token ID for minted tickets
@dev The house address that receives treasuryBalance
@notice The factory address that can create new raffles

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

houseAccount.details: The house address that receives treasuryBalance

nextTokenId.details: global token ID for minted tickets

createRaffle((uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Create a new single-winner raffle, returning its ID.

factory().notice: The factory address that can create new raffles

getRaffleData(uint256).notice: Return data about a raffle, including if winner was picked, etc.

raffleTicketInfo(uint256).notice: tokenId => RaffleTicket info (which raffle, which ticketNumber).

requestRandomNumber(uint256).notice: Called by the owner once the raffle is past its deadline.

soldTickets(uint256,uint256).notice: For each raffle, store a dynamic array of sold ticketNumbers.         e.g. soldTickets[raffleId] = [7, 42, 99, ...]

withdrawHouseBalance(uint256).notice: Withdraw the house's cut for a raffle.
